		"description": "{html}<div><p>In certain cases developers may need to pre-load application\ntabs, for example if they'd like to display a badge right away.</p>\n<p>Currently with the kitchen_sink demo, the badge on the \"UI\" tab\nis only displayed after the user clicks on it, which is not the\nexpected behavior.</p>\n<p>I propose supporting a new XMl element called within in\ntiapp.xml. If set to true, the window's html would be loaded as\nsoon as the tab was created.</p></div>{html}",
